x4freetext: A 7 MV Van de Graaff accelerator
.Three neutron source reactions were used, T(P,N),
D(d,N) and T(d,N) for neutrons of 2.0-3.0, 4.5-9.0
The particle telescopes consisted of delta-e
Five telescopes are set around the
samples at fixed angles, namely at 14, 51, 79, 109 and
141-deg, four proportional counters or energy loss
delta-E3 and delta-E4. Filled  with Ar+CO2(5%)
The remaining energy e1, e2,   e3, e4 and
e5 is measured by either 100-  or 1000-micron-
All samples are 30-mm in diameter self-supporting disks
.Corrections were applied for energy loss in the
proportional counter gas and in the sample.
.The errors include statistical accuracy of foreground
minus background, the uncertainty of the reference
cross-section value and the uncertainty of the mass

.The differential cross section was measured at five
angles. The cross section was determined by fitting
legendre polynomials to the data, and these poly-
nomials were subsequently integrated over all angles.
